Docker-compose allows to run Seahorse locally using Docker. 

Environment variables SEAHORSE_HOST, SEAHORSE_PORT and DATA_DIR must be set.

To start set env variables and run docker-compose:

$ export SEAHORSE_HOST=localhost
$ export SEAHORSE_PORT=8080
$ export DATA_DIR=./data 
$ docker-compose up

Or use wrapper script:

$ ./docker-compose up

Seahorse will start at http://localhost:8080
